modules.description: This module provides functions to bind DOM events—such as mouse, keyboard, drag, and input actions—to handlers, enabling stateful event processing and dynamic behavior. It operates on DOM event objects and a handler type that encapsulates event processing logic and state transitions. Use cases include building interactive UI components, managing real-time form validation, and implementing drag-and-drop functionality with responsive state updates.

Provides functions for parsing and manipulating D3.js-compatible JSON data structures, including hierarchical layouts and force-directed graph representations. Operates on nested records and variant types that model tree and graph data. Enables visualization of network data by computing positions and relationships between nodes and links.

Handles DOM event binding and stateful processing, supporting mouse, keyboard, drag, and input events. It uses event objects and handler types to manage interactions, enabling real-time form validation, drag-and-drop interfaces, and interactive UI elements. Operations include attaching handlers, updating state based on events, and triggering dynamic responses. Examples include tracking user input changes, responding to mouse movements, and managing drag operations with custom state transitions.
